summary: An Ordinance levying the taxes upon the taxable property in the City of Seattle needed to raise sufficient revenue to carry on the different departments of the Municipal Government for the ensuing fiscal year, to-wit: for the year beginning on the first day of January, 1907, and ending on the thirty-first day of December, 1907, including the interest to accrue during said year on the bonded debt of the city, and fixing the rate thereof.
